Wrapper-divergence observability shipped 2026-05-20 ~11:50: gm cf8f98da + gmsniff 36120af. Past iterations exposed that the wasm-version label (v0.1.X) was identical across watchers running different wrapper code. The wrapper is the JS host that loaded the wasm; bumps to wrapper-only files (gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js — e.g. my IDLE_LIMIT_MS 15min→60min fix at 5b4cf8e0) reach downstream only on bootstrap+respawn. Without wrapper-sha visible, agent had no way to verify which watchers had new wrapper without reading each file. Fix: writeStatus() now carries wrapper_sha (first 12 hex chars of sha256, already computed for lock-takeover) + idle_limit_ms (effective per-watcher threshold). gmsniff --watchers renders the column; when multiple distinct shas alive simultaneously they highlight yellow. Self-discipline: 0 violations on parent session 6b78e9f3 past 30m. Conformance confirmed: orient_nouns populates correctly from instruction body prompt; 5 residual.skipped events past 30m were correct gate behavior (open browser sessions + pending PRD on sibling agent), not bugs.